HEADWORD: Biliteral
<hw>Bi*lit"er*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bis</ets> twice + <ets>littera</ets> letter.]</ety> <def>Consisting
of two letters; <as>as, a <ex>biliteral</ex> root of a Sanskrit
verb</as>.</def> <au>Sir W. Jones.</au> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
word, syllable, or root, consisting of two letters.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biliteralism</ent>⟦br⟧
